===Twin towns <U+2014> sister cities===

Chorz<U+00F3>w is [[town twinning|twinned]] with:

* {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Zl<U+00ED>n]], [[Czech Republic]]
* {{flagicon|GER}} [[Iserlohn]], [[Germany]] since 2004
* {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Termoli]], [[Italy]]
* {{flagicon|HUN}} [[<U+00D3>zd]], [[Hungary]]
* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Creil]], [[France]]
* {{flagicon|UKR}} [[Ternopil]], [[Ukraine]]

==People==
Born in Chorz<U+00F3>w:
*[[George Golla]] - Australian jazz musician
*[[Kurt Alder]] (1902-1958) - German chemist, [[Nobel Prize]] in chemistry
*[[August Froehlich]] (1891-1942) - German Roman Catholic priest, member of the resistance against Nazism and martyr
*[[Franz Waxman]] - American composer
*[[Pilars de Pilar|Wlasyslaw Pilars de Pilar]] - [[List of Polish language poets|Polish poet]] and entrepreneur
*[[Ryszard Riedel]] - [[blues-rock]] vocalist
*Karolina Gluck - Polish victim of the [[7 July 2005 London bombings|7/7]] Bombing in [[London]] on July 7, 2005 (killed on the Number 30 bus at [[Tavistock Square|Tavistock square]])
*[[Hanna Schygulla]] - German actress and chanson singer
*[[Walter Mixa]] (born 1941), [[Bishop of Augsburg]] and military Bishop of the [[Bundeswehr]]
*Theodor Kotulla - [[Cinema of Germany|German film]] director
*Olgierd <U+0141>ukaszewicz - Polish actor
*[[Helga Molander]] - German actress, and mother of [[Hans Eysenck]]
*[[G<U+00FC>nther Rittau]] - German cameraman and [[film director]]
*[[Antoni Piechniczek]] - Polish soccer coach (lead twice the national team at [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]])
*[[Tino Schwierzina]] - German politician
*[[Oskar Seidlin]] - American scholar
*[[Gerard Cie<U+015B>lik]] - Polish soccer superstar
*[[Reinhard Appel]] - German journalist
*[[Miros<U+0142>aw Bregu<U+0142>a]] - Polish vocalist, guitarist, composer and founder of [[Music of Poland|Polish music]] group [[Universe]]
*[[Paul Mross]] or Pawe<U+0142> Mr<U+00F3>z - Polish and German chess player
*[[Friedrich Wei<U+00DF>ler]] - lawyer
*[[Gerard Wodarz]], Polish soccer star of the interbellum period,
*[[Leonard Pi<U+0105>tek]], Polish soccer star of the interbellum period.
*[[Adam Taubitz]], German jazz and classic musician.
*[[Janusz Michallik]], former [[United States men's national soccer team|American]] national team soccer player, currently a commentator for [[ESPN]]

Associated with Chorz<U+00F3>w:
*[[Friedrich Wilhelm von Reden]] (1752<U+2013>1815) German pioneer in mining
*[[John Baildon]] (1772<U+2013>1846) Scottish pioneer in metallurgy
*[[Adolph Menzel]] (1815<U+2013>1905) German artist
*[[Ignacy Mo<U+015B>cicki]] (1867<U+2013>1946) Polish chemist and then [[President of the Republic of Poland|President of Poland]]
*[[Fritz Haber]] (1868<U+2013>1934) German chemist
*[[Eugeniusz Kwiatkowski]] (1888<U+2013>1974) eminent Polish economist and politician
*[[Joe Wickham]] (1890<U+2013>1968) Irish sportsperson
*[[Ernst Willimowski|Ernest Wilimowski]] (1916<U+2013>1997) Silesian soccer star
*[[Jerzy Buzek]] (1940- ) Prime minister of Poland, President of the European Parliament

==Accident==
On 28 January 2006, a roof collapsed at an [[Exhibition center|exhibition hall]], killing 65 people. See [[Katowice Trade Hall roof collapse|Trade hall roof collapse in Katowice, Poland]].

